  7. Patent License.

  " patent license" is any express agreement or commitment not to
enforce a patent (such as an express permission to practice a patent
or covenant not to sue for patent infringement).  To "grant" a patent
license to a party means to make such an agreement or commitment not
to enforce a patent against the party.

  If you convey a covered work, knowingly relying on a patent license,
and the Corresponding Application Code is not available for anyone to
copy, free of charge and under the terms of this License, through a
